## Cursor-Specific Features

### Customization Support
- Customizations are loaded from `.bmad-core/customizations/{agent-id}-custom.yaml`
- Use `mdc:.bmad-core/customizations/` prefix for file references in Cursor
- Customizations persist through BMAD updates (gitignored)

### Workflow Initialization
- Use `*workflow-init` to automatically analyze project and recommend workflow
- Works seamlessly in Cursor with file system access
- Updates `.bmad-core/core-config.yaml` with selected workflow

### Enhanced Sharding
- Sharding now includes cross-references for 90% token savings
- Use `*shard-doc` with enhanced cross-reference detection
- Generated `.cross-refs.json` enables intelligent section loading

